198 THE ODES OF HORACE

The Muse bids live the man deserving praise‚ And him in Heaven the muse beatifies 3

Thus Hercules, renowned for toilsome days, At Jupiter's much-envied banquets lies;

Thus the twin stars, the sons of Tyndarus, From the sea's depths snatch vessels tempest- wrecked 3 The vows of men to good conclusions thus

Bacchus conducts‚—-his brows with vine-leaves decked.
